{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782363162322,"sessionID":"ses_102e12f2cffejoPH9Frr5RB4Jr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PFlMreDCEwhFeDR5LMcp49qo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md","limit":260},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Foodike Source Walkthrough\n2: \n3: ## Scope\n4: \n5: - Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n6: - Session type: source walkthrough only, no target translation\n7: - Evidence sources used first: generated reports under `translation-inputs/`, then Kotlin/Android source files where analyzer output looked noisy or ambiguous\n8: \n9: ## Initial Findings\n10: \n11: - The source app is a single-module Android app built with Jetpack Compose, Navigation Compose, Hilt, Accompanist pager/flow layout, splash screen API, and DataStore preferences.\n12: - Most user data is backed by static in-memory fake data in `FakeData.kt` and repository wrappers around that data.\n13: - The only real persisted state is the login flag stored in DataStore preferences.\n14: - Navigation is entirely Compose-based. The app starts at onboarding or home depending on the persisted login state.\n15: - There is no backend API, Room database, Retrofit client, Firebase integration, or true file/media access in the actual source code inspected so far.\n16: - Generated capability templates appear to over-report file/media/permission capabilities based on heuristics. Source inspection is required before accepting those rows as real platform obligations.\n17: \n18: ## Architecture Overview\n19: \n20: ### Entry and app shell\n21: \n22: - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt`\n23:   - Installs Android splash screen.\n24:   - Injects `SplashViewModel`.\n25:   - Uses `FoodikeTheme` and `SetupNavigation(startDestination = screen)`.\n26: - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/common/SplashViewModel.kt`\n27:   - Reads `LoginRepository.loginState.first()` synchronously inside `runBlocking` during init.\n28:   - Chooses `Screen.Home.route` when logged in, otherwise `Screen.Onboarding.route`.\n29:   - Exposes `isLoading` and `startDestination` for splash gating.\n30: \n31: ### Navigation cluster\n32: \n33: - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Screen.kt`\n34:   - Defines routes for onboarding, login, home, history, cart, profile, restaurant details.\n35:   - Includes `withArgs`, though route args are not yet used by the inspected navigation graph.\n36: - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt`\n37:   - `NavigationGraph` wires Compose destinations.\n38:   - `SetupNavigation` owns `NavController`, shared `LazyListState`, and scaffold with bottom bar.\n39:   - Bottom bar is shown only on `home` and `history` when the shared list is scrolled to the top.\n40:   - Floating action button navigates to cart.\n41: \n42: ### Data and state clusters\n43: \n44: - `data/data_source/FakeData.kt`\n45:   - Large static fixture file defining menus, ads, restaurants, favourites, and cart seed items.\n46:   - Serves as the content source for home, history, detail, and cart flows.\n47: - `data/repository/HomeRepositoryImpl.kt`\n48:   - Returns fake restaurants, ads, and recommended items.\n49:   - Resolves restaurant details by exact name match.\n50: - `data/repository/UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt`\n51:   - Keeps mutable in-memory app session state:\n52:   - `currentRestaurant`\n53:   - menu item cart counts for selected restaurant\n54:   - favourites list clone\n55:   - cart item list clone\n56:   - Exposes these through `Flow` builders that emit current snapshots.\n57: - `data/repository/LoginRepositoryImpl.kt`\n58:   - Persists a boolean login flag with DataStore preferences.\n59:   - `toggleLoginState()` flips the stored value.\n60: \n61: ### UI domains\n62: \n63: - Onboarding: introductory pager and CTA to login.\n64: - Login: email/password entry, snackbar messaging, login action toggling persisted session state.\n65: - Home: top location/search/actions, ad carousel, filters, recommended categories, favourite restaurants, restaurant list.\n66: - Restaurant detail: selected restaurant summary, liked state, expandable menu sections, item add/subtract interactions.\n67: - History: tabbed history/favourites presentation.\n68: - Cart: selected items, coupon entry, bill, delivery section.\n69: - Profile: profile card and logout action.\n70: \n71: ## File-By-File Walkthrough\n72: \n73: This section starts with confirmed files. Remaining files will be appended as inspection continues.\n74: \n75: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt`\n76: \n77: - Role: Android entry activity and Compose host.\n78: - Key classes/types: `MainActivity`\n79: - Key methods/functions: `onCreate`\n80: - User-facing features:\n81:   - Splash screen remains visible while startup state resolves.\n82:   - App opens into onboarding or home depending on stored login state.\n83: - Data/state behavior:\n84:   - Reads reactive state from `SplashViewModel.startDestination` and `isLoading`.\n85: - Side effects:\n86:   - Calls Android splash screen API and Compose `setContent`.\n87: - Resource/id evidence:\n88:   - Uses app theme through `FoodikeTheme`.\n89: - Dependency evidence:\n90:   - `androidx.core.splashscreen`, Compose activity, Hilt injection.\n91: - Migration notes:\n92:   - Target should keep a startup gate that resolves persisted session state before initial route selection.\n93: \n94: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/common/SplashViewModel.kt`\n95: \n96: - Role: startup route resolver.\n97: - Key classes/types: `SplashViewModel`\n98: - Key methods/functions: initializer logic only.\n99: - User-facing features:\n100:   - Logged-in users skip onboarding/login and land on home.\n101:   - Logged-out users land on onboarding.\n102: - Data/state behavior:\n103:   - `MutableStateFlow<Boolean>` for loading.\n104:   - `MutableState<String>` for start destination.\n105:   - Reads first login-state emission synchronously.\n106: - Side effects:\n107:   - Blocking read of login state in `init`.\n108: - Resource/id evidence: none.\n109: - Dependency evidence:\n110:   - `LoginRepository`, coroutines flow, Compose mutable state.\n111: - Migration notes:\n112:   - Preserve the behavior, but Harmony target should avoid blocking init if there is a non-blocking startup pattern.\n113: \n114: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Screen.kt`\n115: \n116: - Role: route registry.\n117: - Key classes/types: `Screen` sealed class with `Onboarding`, `LoginScreen`, `Home`, `History`, `Cart`, `Profile`, `RestaurantDetails`.\n118: - Key methods/functions: `withArgs`\n119: - User-facing features:\n120:   - Defines available navigation destinations.\n121: - Data/state behavior:\n122:   - Static route constants.\n123: - Side effects: none.\n124: - Resource/id evidence: route strings are hardcoded.\n125: - Dependency evidence: navigation layer references this file.\n126: - Migration notes:\n127:   - Keep route/domain separation in target navigation model.\n128: \n129: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt`\n130: \n131: - Role: navigation graph, scaffold shell, bottom navigation behavior.\n132: - Key classes/types: none.\n133: - Key methods/functions: `NavigationGraph`, `SetupNavigation`, `BottomBar`\n134: - User-facing features:\n135:   - Hosts onboarding, login, home, history, cart, profile, and restaurant-detail screens.\n136:   - Shows bottom navigation only on home/history and only when the shared list is at top.\n137:   - Shows floating cart button centered above bottom bar.\n138:   - Bottom bar items navigate to home/history with state restoration semantics.\n139: - Data/state behavior:\n140:   - Owns `NavController`.\n141:   - Owns shared `LazyListState` and derives whether first visible item index is zero.\n142:   - Reads current back stack route for conditional shell rendering.\n143: - Side effects:\n144:   - Navigation commands mutate back stack.\n145: - Resource/id evidence:\n146:   - `R.string.home`, `R.string.history`, `R.drawable.ic_baseline_assignment_24`.\n147: - Dependency evidence:\n148:   - Navigation Compose, Accompanist pager opt-in, Compose Scaffold and material icons.\n149: - Migration notes:\n150:   - Shell visibility depends on both route and scroll position, not route alone.\n151:   - There is a duplicated onboarding destination block in the graph; likely harmless but should be noted during planning.\n152: \n153: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/LoginRepositoryImpl.kt`\n154: \n155: - Role: persisted login/session-state repository.\n156: - Key classes/types: `LoginRepositoryImpl`, `PrefsDataStore`\n157: - Key methods/functions: `loginState`, `toggleLoginState`\n158: - User-facing features:\n159:   - Login/logout state survives app restarts.\n160: - Data/state behavior:\n161:   - DataStore preference file `user_login_state_pref`.\n162:   - Boolean key `user_login_state` defaults to `false`.\n163:   - `toggleLoginState` inverts current value.\n164: - Side effects:\n165:   - Writes to Android DataStore preferences.\n166: - Resource/id evidence: preference file and key names hardcoded.\n167: - Dependency evidence:\n168:   - AndroidX DataStore preferences.\n169: - Migration notes:\n170:   - This is one of the few true platform capabilities and should map to HarmonyOS persistent preferences storage.\n171: \n172: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/HomeRepositoryImpl.kt`\n173: \n174: - Role: static content repository for home-related lists.\n175: - Key classes/types: `HomeRepositoryImpl`\n176: - Key methods/functions: `getRestaurants`, `getAds`, `getFoodItems`, `getRestaurantFromName`\n177: - User-facing features:\n178:   - Home screen gets restaurant list, advertisements, and recommended food categories.\n179:   - Restaurant detail lookup resolves by tapped restaurant name.\n180: - Data/state behavior:\n181:   - Wraps top-level fake lists from `FakeData.kt`.\n182: - Side effects: none.\n183: - Resource/id evidence:\n184:   - Downstream data references drawable resources through models.\n185: - Dependency evidence:\n186:   - `Results`, fake data lists.\n187: - Migration notes:\n188:   - Preserve repository boundary even if fake data remains temporary in target early phases.\n189: \n190: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt`\n191: \n192: - Role: in-memory session repository for selected restaurant, favourites, menu counters, and cart items.\n193: - Key classes/types: `UserDataRepositoryImpl`\n194: - Key methods/functions: `setRestaurant`, `getSavedRestaurant`, `getMenuItems`, `getLikedRestaurants`, `isRestaurantLiked`, `getCartItems`\n195: - User-facing features:\n196:   - Selecting a restaurant establishes the detail screen context.\n197:   - Detail screen can read menu items with mutable counts.\n198:   - History/favourites reflects mutable favourites list.\n199:   - Cart reads initial mutable cart list snapshot.\n200: - Data/state behavior:\n201:   - `menuList` is a mutable set of `CartItem` built from current restaurant menu with zero counts.\n202:   - `currentRestaurant` holds active detail context.\n203:   - `list` holds mutable favourites list copy.\n204:   - `cartListItems` holds mutable cart list copy.\n205:   - Each getter emits a one-shot flow snapshot.\n206: - Side effects:\n207:   - Mutates in-memory process state only.\n208: - Resource/id evidence: indirect through model images.\n209: - Dependency evidence:\n210:   - Kotlin flows, fake-data favourite/cart lists.\n211: - Migration notes:\n212:   - Source behavior is session-scoped and not persisted except login state.\n213:   - Later planning should decide whether target keeps this as app-memory state or adds persistence for better resilience; either choice should preserve visible behavior first.\n214: \n215: ### `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/data_source/FakeData.kt`\n216: \n217: - Role: static fixture and seed content authority.\n218: - Key classes/types: top-level lists of `MenuItem`, `Restaurant`, `Advertisement`, `FoodItem`, `CartItem`.\n219: - Key methods/functions: none.\n220: - User-facing features:\n221:   - Restaurant cards, detail pages, ads, recommended categories, favourites, and cart contents all originate here.\n222:   - Vegetarian/non-vegetarian sections, prices, ratings, counts, estimated delivery times, and imagery are all encoded here.\n223: - Data/state behavior:\n224:   - Pure immutable seed data.\n225: - Side effects: none.\n226: - Resource/id evidence:\n227:   - Strong use of `R.drawable.*` for restaurant, food, ad, profile, and icon visuals.\n228: - Dependency evidence:\n229:   - Domain model layer and Android drawable resources.\n230: - Migration notes:\n231:   - This file is business-content-heavy, not platform-capability-heavy.\n232:   - Generated reports that infer file/media/permissions from this file are false positives so far.\n233: \n234: ### `app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`\n235: \n236: - Role: Android app declaration.\n237: - Key classes/types: `application`, `activity`, launcher intent filter.\n238: - Key methods/functions: none.\n239: - User-facing features:\n240:   - Declares launcher activity and app icon/label.\n241:   - Enables backup/data-extraction rules.\n242:   - Applies splash theme to app and activity.\n243: - Data/state behavior: none directly.\n244: - Side effects:\n245:   - Registers Android entrypoints.\n246: - Resource/id evidence:\n247:   - `@xml/data_extraction_rules`, `@xml/backup_rules`, `@mipmap/ic_launcher`, `@string/app_name`, `@style/Theme.SplashScreenTheme`.\n248: - Dependency evidence:\n249:   - `FoodikeApp`, `MainActivity`.\n250: - Migration notes:\n251:   - No dangerous permissions declared.\n252:   - No deep links, services, receivers, or providers.\n253: \n254: ### `app/build.gradle.kts`\n255: \n256: - Role: Android app module build configuration.\n257: - Key classes/types: none.\n258: - Key methods/functions: none.\n259: - User-facing features:\n260:   - Enables Compose and splash/navigation/data store dependencies used by runtime behavior.\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 376. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Foodike Source Walkthrough\n\n## Scope\n\n- Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n- Session type: source walkthrough only, no target translation\n- Evidence sources used first: generated reports under `translation-inputs/`, then Kotlin/Android source files where analyzer output looked noisy or ambiguous\n\n## Initial Findings\n\n- The source app is a single-module Android app built with Jetpack Compose, Navigation Compose, Hilt, Accompanist pager/flow layout, splash screen API, and DataStore preferences.\n- Most user data is backed by static in-memory fake data in `FakeData.kt` and repository wrappers around that data.\n- The only real persisted state is the login flag stored in DataStore preferences.\n- Navigation is entirely Compose-based. The app starts at onboarding or home depending on the persisted login state.\n- There is no backend API, Room database, Retrofit client, Firebase integration, or true file/media access in the actual source code inspected so far.\n- Generated capability templates appear to over-report file/media/permission capabilities based on heuristics. Source inspection is required before accepting those rows as real platform obligations.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### Entry and app shell","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md","time":{"start":1782363162316,"end":1782363162321}},"id":"prt_efd1f869c001hl6Am3s1Aj5mA7","sessionID":"ses_102e12f2cffejoPH9Frr5RB4Jr","messageID":"msg_efd1f6765001a2C1kW2Pe60NIb"}}
